<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 01 at 1:32AM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...HEAVY RAINFALL WITH SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS DURING THE LATE
NIGHT...
WEATHER...
* A large band of showers and thunderstorms will move into the
region, mainly along and west of the I-75 corridor, and last
until about 400 AM.
* Heavy rainfall is the primary hazard with totals near 1 inch
possible.
IMPACTS...
* Heavy rainfall will reduce visibility for motorists and produce
ponding of water on area roads.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for variable
driving conditions by slowing down and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
